txt.en:
'Every animal contributes a purpose and a value to all the others. When one is removed the others will suffer.

'The Corsairs have spread snares all over Tol Fennas to try and catch the rabbits and squirrels and other small creatures. These creatures allow the forests to grow and the larger creatures to exist.

'Take a boat from the dock to Tol Fennas. Once there, remove any snares you find. I expect they will not be hard to find.'
Dimlas is in Dol Amroth.\n\nDimlas will be pleased to hear some snares have been removed.
The Corsairs have spread snares all over Tol Fennas to try and catch the smaller creatures.
'I am sure they will place more, but every day and bit we can delay them is a victory for us.'
Snares can be found on Tol Fennas.\n\nDimlas asked you to head to Tol Fennas and remove the snares the Corsairs have placed. A boat in the harbour of Dol Amroth can take you to Tol Fennas.
